features: [Space for Every Pair] With a length of 38.8'', 4-5 pairs of shoes can comfortably sit on each shelf, totaling to 20-25 pairs. The 6.7'' spacing between the shelves allows you to store any type of footwear, from sneakers to high heels
[Easy to Assemble] Parts separated in different bags, labeled parts, and clear instructions provide you with everything you need to put this 5-tier shoe rack together quickly and easily
[Lightweight yet Strong] Constructed with non-woven fabric shelves, metal tube frames, and sturdy plastic connectors, this shoe rack is lightweight yet strong to hold up to 11 lb per tier
[Saves Space] This slim, vertical shoe rack maximizes your storage space in the entryway or closet while minimizing floor space, making it ideal for small spaces
[Easy to Maintain and Move] All you need is a damp cloth to clean the metal or fabric. When you want to move this shoe shelf to change things up a little, its lightweight design makes it a breeze
body.description: Keep your shoes organized with this Songmics 5 Tiers Shoe Rack, which is designed to provide a great storage solution for your collection of favorite footwear. It is constructed out of durable iron pipes, non-woven fabric and plastic connectors. Each shelf holds up to 3 or 4 pairs of full-size shoes. This is a decent rack to store your shoes and fits well into you doorway, entryway, mud room, bedroom, closet and so on. This space-saving shoe rack could also be put in a corner or in a hall.Specifications: - Color: Black - Material: strengthened metal pipes, non-woven fabrics tiers, plastic connectors - Layer Height: 6.7" (17 cm)- Assembly Required: Yes - Weight: 4.4 lbs (2kg) - Product Size (L x W x H): 39.4'' x 11.1'' x 36.3'' (100 x 28 x 92 cm)Shipping List:- 1 x 5 Tier Shoe Rack- 1 x Instruction

reviews.reviewText: Great product, I'm using it as a shoe rack. Perfect size and holds 20 pair of my sneakers (men sneakers size 10) very comfortably. Easy to put together and is very sturdy and light weight. Will purchase another one and will definitely recommend to family and friends.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 31, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good, reasonably sturdy set of shoe shelves at a good price
reviews.reviewText: This shelf will need a wall to go against but gives a ton of space for shoes, looks very nice, and is pretty sturdy for the price. It is big enough, and not so sturdy that you can get away with making it free-standing. It definitely needs to be anchored to the wall. The anchors (one for each side) aren't going to let kids climb on them -- they're just drywall screws with a place to connect a zip tie. There was quite a bit of work to put them together but it isn't difficult, just tedious.These are a great value and pretty sturdy for the price. Don't confuse them with a custom shoe shelf or anything like that -- they're an inexpensive set of shoe shelves with a ton of space for a low price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 31, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Wow! I had my doubts that this shoe rack would live up to my expectations. So much so, that I ordered an additional shoe rack made by another company with almost identical specs from Amazon and placed it with this order (Just in case this one was a dud). Well let me just say that it's NOT A DUD, in fact it's great ! It's sturdy, well balanced and seems to be durable. I, 100%, wasn't expecting to get five pairs of a shoes to a shelf, but I was wrong. As you can see from my pics I have five pair on each shelf and one shelf has 6 pairs (flats) There's a mix of men's, women's and kids shoes, All types, sneakers, boots, heels, sandals, it's all up there and they all fit.. The heels I turned on their sides so they wouldn't wobble and even turned on their sides I still got five pair of shoes on the shelf! Putting it together was easy, well, easy once I figured out that you need to build each shelf (have all four sides in place) and then place it down onto the shelf below it, tap it down with a rubber mallet and move forward. Easy peasy took about 12 minutes. I love this shoe rack so much that I ordered two more today. Oh and I did open and assemble the other rack that I mentioned earlier and the quality just wasn't there. The shelf material was flimsy, the bars that make the length of the shelves had to be connected in the middle to achieve the length of each shelf. Whereas the songmics is one long bar, no connections in the middle. And The plastic connectors that hold everything together, they felt less durable than the songmics connectors.. Bottom line, this is a great purchase you won't be sorry!

reviews.reviewTitle: Great rack, takes a bit of time to put together, but lots of storage especially for smaller shoes.
reviews.reviewText: I used this for shoe storage in my basement (on carpet), and because it's not a perfectly flat surface, I had to attach it to the wall at the top/back in order to ensure it would not fall over when full. That being said, it does seem fairly sturdy, and I don't think it would be a problem on hardwood/concrete/tile, etc. It did take a bit of time to put together as it comes in a lot of small parts (2 rods per "shelf" - a long piece of canvas with holes along each side, 4 plastic connectors per shelf, and then 4 small rods in between each "shelf"). Once I got the hang of it (one the 4th shelf or so), it went a lot faster, just don't miss a part or put the bracket the wrong way! Overall, I'm very happy with it! If you have ankle boots with more than 6-7 inches of height they'll have to squeeze in a bit, but for flatter shoes/runners/sandals, it's great, and I was able to fit more pairs per row, about 6 pairs of runners or 8 pairs of sandals!Would buy again for sure!
Llegó en tiempo y forma. Fácil de armar y muy útil. Muy práctico y funcional. Sí le caben 5 pares de zapatos (tenis de hombre) por nivel.
